<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> element (definition description) provides the description, definition, or value for the preceding <a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a> element(s) in a <a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> (definition list).</p>
    <p>By default, <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements are indented from the left margin to visually distinguish them from their associated terms.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Definitions for glossary terms</li>
      <li>Values in metadata displays</li>
      <li>Answers in FAQ sections</li>
      <li>Values in key-value pairs</li>
      <li>Product attribute values</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not to Use</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Outside of a <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> element</li>
      <li>Without a preceding <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> element</li>
      <li>For regular list content &mdash; use <a href="/docs/elements/native/li/"><code>&lt;li&gt;</code></a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-basic.html" url="dl-basic.html" title="Basic definition descriptions" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic definition list">{{ basicListCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Multiple Descriptions</h2>
    <p>A term can have multiple <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements, each providing a different definition, meaning, or aspect.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-multiple-descriptions.html" url="dl-multiple-descriptions.html" title="Multiple descriptions" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Multiple descriptions for one term">{{ multipleDescriptionsCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Shared Description</h2>
    <p>Multiple terms can share the same <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> description. This is useful for synonyms or alternate names.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/dl-multiple-terms.html" url="dl-multiple-terms.html" title="Shared description" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Multiple terms sharing a description">{{ sharedDescriptionCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Rich Content</h2>
    <p>Definition descriptions can contain any flow content, including paragraphs, lists, links, and more.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/dd-rich-content.html" url="dd-rich-content.html" title="Rich content in descriptions" shadow></browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Description with nested list">{{ nestedListCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Rich content in description">{{ richDescriptionCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Screen Reader Behavior</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Announced as the description or definition for preceding terms</li>
      <li>Associated with <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> elements in the list context</li>
      <li>Multiple descriptions announced sequentially</li>
      <li>Rich content within descriptions is fully accessible</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Write clear, meaningful descriptions</li>
      <li>Use appropriate semantic elements within descriptions</li>
      <li>Ensure every <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> is associated with at least one <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Use lists or paragraphs within <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> for complex content</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Properties</h2>

    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Property</th>
          <th>Value</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>margin-inline-start</code></td>
          <td><code>var(--size-l)</code></td>
          <td>Left indentation to distinguish from terms</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>When a <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> is followed by a <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> (starting a new term group), <code>dd + dt</code> adds <code>margin-block-start: var(--size-m)</code> for visual separation.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Model</h2>

    <h3>Permitted Content</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Flow content (paragraphs, lists, figures)</li>
      <li>Inline elements (links, code, emphasis)</li>
      <li>Nested definition lists</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Required Parent</h3>
    <p>Must be a child of <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code>, optionally inside a <code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dl/"><code>&lt;dl&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Definition list container (required parent)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/dt/"><code>&lt;dt&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Definition term (required sibling)</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/dl-item/"><code>&lt;dl-item&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Custom element for grouping dt/dd pairs</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/ul/"><code>&lt;ul&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Can be nested inside <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> for detailed lists</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/ol/"><code>&lt;ol&gt;</code></a> &mdash; Can be nested inside <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> for sequential details</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

